That&#39;s the whole point. If the scenario is, as Tim explained earlier, that
the data change is indeed braking (because driven by changing requirements),
that won&#39;t help in any way.

But if you are going to support multiple clients, you may as well make
decisions early in your media type design to avoid multiplication of
formats, by ensuring extensibility, error recovery, and non-destructive
updates, and you should be in a much better place than having two media
types, be it that you support them at the same time or not.



